@mbob4337 More. From the terminal entries in game in implies that ALL stars are gone. And probably ALL planets too (the report just makes a point about not being able to find previously known habitable or resource-rich worlds). Leaving a bunch of orphaned starships and space stations. 
So yeah it's basically waiting until they run out of energy to continue. Hence all the eggs being in the basket of exploring this mysterious blood-covered moon.
I thought at first it WAS the literal biblical rapture, but you, the Coalition of Iron and Eden were sent to purgutory/hell. Not that the universe was literally stripped bare barring the blood moon.

@TetraScale There are a lot of clues that seem to imply it IS the Biblical Rapture. For one, in Revelations the Stars do dissapear, and the Moon is covered in Blood (along with all oceans/rivers being turned into Blood). The Main Character mentions having a Tattoo forced on him, and the COI tried burning it off, later he takes off bandages on his arms and sees soars and boils, this is because those who get the mark of the beast end up getting soars and boils.
   There are a few other things that aren't as clear-cut, like the bright light he encounters being a star, potentially the one in Revelations that has the keys to the "pit" (basically Hell) that falls into the ocean. The reason its possibly that is because in the game files its called the Void which is another name for the Pit, and it resembles a star. There is also the fact that the Eyeball that the game is famous for is snake-like, and in the movie it convinces a woman to eat the blood I think, so might be a reference to Satan or at least Leviathan. And the main monster, the Anglerfish looking thing, in the files its called Frog, and anglers are Frogfish, and there are only 2 references to frogs in the Bible, and one is in Revelations (I don't remember what it is or does though, also the first mention is the Plague of Egypt). Also the Eyeball and the Anglerfish are 2 different creatures, since the creator made a video for some audio, and the picture used was by him and depicts a different creature from the Anglerfish looking one, and it has the eyeball. Its a bit flimsy I know, but why else would he design them so differently?
  I know its not the most compelling evidence, but considering the creator of the game is open about being a Christian, and the many biblical references (Eden, Rapture, etc.), it seems reasonable enough.

